Peter Dada, Akure There was pandemonium at Oja Oba Area of Akure, the capital of Ondo State on Tuesday morning as members of the state chapter of the National Union of Road Transport Workers engaged in free for all. This came barely 48 hours after the factional unionists fought at the Owode area of the state, causing injuries to many people. On Tuesday, it was gathered that the residents and traders in the popular Oba Adesida Road had to run for their lives while the business activities were paralysed when the armed unionists attacked each other. Some vehicles were also vandalised by the fighters. The cause of the fight was still unknown as of the time of filing this report. Details laterâ€¦ 